<br>
Earlier that night, as Hope had completed her journey toward Lesvos, she had been met near a nighttime campfire by Genesis Tiberon, who was very displeased with her reasons for being there. Hope assured her no harm would come of Lesvos. She had but two more lands to visit before her travels were complete. Given Genesis' powers, Hope assured her that if something unfortunate should happen, Gen could always catch up to Hope easily enough and seek her own justice. Genesis seemed content with that as she remained by the campfire. Hope traveled under the dark of moonlight to the water shore. A large raft was waiting for Hope and her horse. She had steadied her horse's nerves and led him onto the raft... <br>
<br>
...a large water raft did approach the shoreline of Lesvos. Any who were nearby could see the shape of a horse on the raft. The horse belonged to Hope. When the raft brushed up against the sand shore, the  horse stepped off the raft onto Lesvos. The animal was well cared for and some supplies were on the saddle. But the horse was alone. <br>
<br>
Hope had wisely chosen to separate from her horse. There was no immediate proof of her arrival, though it was very certain a horse would not appear on its own. She was here somewhere. Any who were there to meet the horse would be wise to suspect as much. Hope was somewhere on the island at this time, having landed elsewhere on her own, using the darkness of night and the sounds of nature from the forest to hide her movements, as she moved toward the central Lesvos tribal area..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 359<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(6/8/02 2:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sences</span><hr size=1> ~ Artemis tood with the small army by the only gates leading into the fortress area. Within the walled fortress was the only area that would be of any use to Hope, but luckily, everything that Hope seemed to want from the other tribes had been warded and bound, she would not, NOT be able to touch, move or locate them. Melousa and Velaska had made sure of that. As did the other tribes before Velaska's rule here on Lesvos. She had gained word by her spys in the woods that Hope had arrived on the island, and Artemis tood ready, with her bow and arrow prepared, the same Arrows Zeus had gifted to her that would destroy any immortal who it came into contact with, and Artemis was a sure shot. She had tired of this Hope being, and was more then prepared to use them.~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umistressmoranna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress Moranna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/morannadracul/images/flameheart.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(6/8/02 10:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Wickedest One of All Appears</span><hr size=1> ~ Out of the shadows it seems she walked, and over to the gang by the gates of the fortress. She wore a simple leather cat suit, her hair pulled up into a high ponytail. She looked around.~<br>
