<br>
There was some time of silence as each of them took in their surroundings and those Amazons protectors who stood before them. Hope had desired a quiet approach and infiltration into the fortress, but with the spies moving in the forest, she had resigned herself to the truth it was but a matter of time. Still, she was not the one imposing an immediate threat. It was the raft owner who held a blade to the spies throat.<br>
<br>
Hope's eyes moved to each of the women before her. She had past dealings with Artemis and Demeter. While she did not remember any encounters with Velaska, Melousa, Eponin or Moranna, she assumed that each were capable in the skills of war. Amazons seemed to be trained from birth for such things. In another time and place, under different circumstances, Hope would have found great use for that. For now.. her purpose was more subtle and direct. She remained in silent observation of the women in the short distance.<br>
<br>
The raft owner held a nervous look in his eyes as he held the spy closely, the blade but inches from the man's throat. It was the raft owner who first spoke ... demanding answers from no one in particular, threatening to attack anyone who approached him. His peculiar behavior likely held by myth and rumors of how Amazons regarded men ... perhaps it was something more. <br>
<br>
Hope remained silent of that....<br>
<br>
He was making himself known to all as the first issue to be dealt with.<br>
His safety and safe passage, or a dead spy and any others who interfered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/tsianina2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 505<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(6/9/02 1:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/varia3sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Var and her army</span><hr size=1> Varia came out of the fortress after sending a messenger to gather her troops, and she walked up next to Velaska, sword drawn. &quot;I'm ready this time,&quot; she snarled, war paint on her face, her amazon leathers on her body. <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#ff0000"> ~Varia Angelina Avande~ </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ubailywesston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baily Wesston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(6/9/02 1:17 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/bailysm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Var and her army</span><hr size=1> Baily wasn't much of a fighter, she was normally calm and reserved, but she could certainly kick ass if needed, and her tribe was being threatened. Her skills were great with the sais, even though she rarely used them, she'd had enough practice to be able to take someone out rather quickly. She emerged from the fortress and joined the group of Amazons, goddesses, and witch, to oppose the dark